 This post was made about some real life friends of mine and after letting all the fire burn out of this one i would like to add my two copper. I rarely read these boards and found out about this through word of mouth. I thought i would put the finishing touches and my view on this thread. Although i have no doubts that the groups that had their wrongful deaths in KC that night were quite hot over the situation and feel they have gotten justification flaming a few level 60's on the boards the information i got from Xantres and Faad, and a few people who were the recipients of the lot of dogmen cuz i am 51 and group their often, is that the process in which mobs were gathered was not unlike the late night tactics any strong group might do in any zone. If you all would look inside yerselves and see that this may have been 50% the fact that you died and 50% the fact that yer group could not pull off such pulling techniques this may all have been avoided. From a few friends other than the ones labelled for wrong doing but yet were not directly involved it seemed that after it happened there was no attempt to ask for a reason for the events or tells to the group involved but an immediate flame zone wide thru /ooc or shout which puts people on the defensive right off and the fact that they offered CR and rez assistance was more than i would probably feel compelled to do if i had been flamed over zone wide chat. As far as Faad and Xantres are concerned they have a reputation of going above and beyond for just about everyone who asks, whether it is pulling in hate, and fear on pick up raids, helping a guild out in the hole during a complete wipeout, helping countless people with their epic pieces, summoning corpses even if having to travel several zones to do this, and much more. In addition i have never and i repeat never seen them maliciously do something to anyone in game which is what FD'ers get labelled for whether they do or not it seems. This post is as much for the people in KC that night as it is for the guild in which these people have decided to play their game with. I just wish people when angry would sit and think about it for a few minutes before they take it to the boards in anger and perhaps tarnish the reputation of people to gain some sort of vengence that what they felt was a wrongful death. I am not trying to down play how you must have felt that night only providing an account of the last two years i have played with these folks. You all know them from one night, i have played with them for two years and I can say that it might of happened exactly the way you said it in the post, although i have my concerns that it was exaggerated due to anger, and will tell you that if you give these people a tell in game you may here their side and how it differs from yours and see a true sense of empathy for yer deaths for they too over the course of playing have probably had the same thing happen to them..my plea to these rants and flames boards in general is dont take things here unless you attempt to get explanation from the group in tells and get an answer like EAD or something. When you die, flame the group that pulled the mobs in zone wide chat, deny their concern for yer group and offer to help with cr and getting yer exp returned to you in the form of exp rez, and then try to tarnish their reps on the boards, and never attempt once to hear their side by giving them a tell then this game would be all about people hating each other and i for one would like to see less of this. My apologies go out to the groups involved in the wipeout cuz i hate to hear those things and empathized with how you must have felt, and to the group of people targetted in this flame for having to defend themselves to their friends and guilds...<br>
